WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:08.466 --> 00:00:11.219 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] ♪ A longing for
miracles that can inspire! ♪

00:00:11.302 --> 00:00:12.929 position:50% align:center
♪ Awaken returner! ♪

00:00:13.013 --> 00:00:14.514 position:50% align:center
♪ Let your heart feel desire! ♪

00:00:14.597 --> 00:00:15.890 position:50% align:center
♪ Excitement! ♪

00:00:15.974 --> 00:00:19.436 position:50% align:center
♪ Take joy wherever you can,
give, it, to, me! ♪

00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:21.438 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
My name's Maimai Yuzuriha!

00:00:21.521 --> 00:00:23.148 position:50% align:center
I'm a second-year
in high school!

00:00:23.231 --> 00:00:27.068 position:50% align:center
And yes, I'm aware that
Maimai is an unusual name.

00:00:28.778 --> 00:00:29.988 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 7A gasps]

00:00:31.823 --> 00:00:33.700 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
I broke them again.

00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:37.579 position:50% align:center
That's okay!
Now they're kaleidoscopes!

00:00:39.497 --> 00:00:42.125 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] Anyway, it's time for
me to go to the public bath!

00:00:42.208 --> 00:00:46.087 position:50% align:center
Ah, I always look forward
to that nice hot water!

00:00:47.172 --> 00:00:49.424 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Afternoon!

00:00:49.507 --> 00:00:52.677 position:50% align:center
Let's see, the women's
bath is that way?

00:01:00.894 --> 00:01:02.937 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] The bath is great,
but the real treat

00:01:03.021 --> 00:01:06.399 position:50% align:center
is that yummy fruit milk
I get to drink right after!

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:10.195 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Refreshment, here I co--!

00:01:46.648 --> 00:01:51.027 position:50% align:center
[KOTARO] Guess what, everyone?
W-We got a new member.

00:01:51.111 --> 00:01:52.278 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:01:52.362 --> 00:01:54.614 position:50% align:center
Give it up for Franchouchou's
Number Seven.

00:01:54.698 --> 00:01:55.740 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Uh...

00:01:55.824 --> 00:01:57.450 position:50% align:center
Can't hear you!

00:01:57.534 --> 00:01:59.160 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] I'm sorry, sir,
I don't understand--

00:01:59.244 --> 00:02:01.287 position:50% align:center
You really need me to
spell it out for you?

00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:03.915 position:50% align:center
You went to the public bath
because ours is broken, right?

00:02:03.998 --> 00:02:06.584 position:50% align:center
And you came back with
what I hope isn't a dead body.

00:02:06.668 --> 00:02:09.212 position:50% align:center
Oh, the zombies have
a problem with corpses now?

00:02:09.295 --> 00:02:10.338 position:50% align:center
[AI]
So she is dead?

00:02:10.422 --> 00:02:11.631 position:50% align:center
You should take
a look at yourselves

00:02:11.715 --> 00:02:13.925 position:50% align:center
before you throw around
the d-word, babe!

00:02:14.009 --> 00:02:15.093 position:50% align:center
[SAKI]
That's not an answer!

00:02:15.176 --> 00:02:16.970 position:50% align:center
Sshhh, hey! It's cool!

00:02:17.053 --> 00:02:18.388 position:50% align:center
After all,
what's one more zombie

00:02:18.471 --> 00:02:20.223 position:50% align:center
to add to the idol
army of the dead?

00:02:20.306 --> 00:02:21.474 position:50% align:center
Oh crap, this is bad!

00:02:21.558 --> 00:02:23.101 position:50% align:center
Where exactly did you find her?

00:02:23.184 --> 00:02:24.644 position:50% align:center
[KOTARO]
Hm? What did you say?

00:02:24.728 --> 00:02:25.729 position:50% align:center
Something dumb?

00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:28.398 position:50% align:center
Come now, I didn't
find her, per se.

00:02:28.481 --> 00:02:31.026 position:50% align:center
It's more like the universe
guided me to her--

00:02:31.109 --> 00:02:33.069 position:50% align:center
--[AI] How's that?
--[KOTARO] How should I know?

00:02:33.153 --> 00:02:35.488 position:50% align:center
We've been to temples
and shrines all over Saga,

00:02:35.572 --> 00:02:37.615 position:50% align:center
maybe I pissed off
some ancient god!

00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:39.993 position:50% align:center
Whoa, Shades. Did you...

00:02:40.076 --> 00:02:43.329 position:50% align:center
No, I'm innocent.
I didn't do squat!

00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:44.789 position:50% align:center
[LILY]
You've got red on you.

00:02:44.873 --> 00:02:45.874 position:50% align:center
Then how did--

00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.960 position:50% align:center
[KOTARO]
Look, you gotta believe me!

00:02:54.215 --> 00:02:56.885 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:02:58.136 --> 00:03:01.389 position:50% align:center
[ALL scream]

00:03:11.441 --> 00:03:12.609 position:50% align:center
No, no, it's heading
right toward us!

00:03:12.692 --> 00:03:14.819 position:50% align:center
Chill out, dead bodies
don't move on their own!

00:03:14.903 --> 00:03:15.820 position:50% align:center
Says the zombie!

00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:18.323 position:50% align:center
But I thought it was only us!

00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:22.243 position:50% align:center
[JUNKO, AI, SAKURA gasp]

00:03:27.123 --> 00:03:28.958 position:50% align:center
Hey. Do you think
you could maybe

00:03:29.042 --> 00:03:31.211 position:50% align:center
tell us whether
you're dead or not?

00:03:31.294 --> 00:03:33.588 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh, did I die?

00:03:33.672 --> 00:03:34.839 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Huh?

00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:35.924 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Hm?

00:03:36.007 --> 00:03:37.050 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Huh?!

00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:46.601 position:50% align:center
[AI] I can't believe you
didn't check to make sure.

00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:48.311 position:50% align:center
[JUNKO] You might not be
a murderer, but this means

00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:50.605 position:50% align:center
that you've abducted
a high-school student.

00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:52.982 position:50% align:center
You think she knows
that we're zombies yet?

00:03:53.066 --> 00:03:54.442 position:50% align:center
Looks that way.

00:03:54.526 --> 00:03:57.195 position:50% align:center
I mean, she's starin' into
your lack of a soul, Sakura.

00:03:59.447 --> 00:04:01.157 position:50% align:center
That's not good,
but at least she hasn't

00:04:01.241 --> 00:04:02.450 position:50% align:center
figured out that
we're Franchouchou.

00:04:02.534 --> 00:04:04.160 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] Um, are you
Franchouchou's Number One?

00:04:04.244 --> 00:04:05.578 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:04:05.662 --> 00:04:07.956 position:50% align:center
That's right!
I knew she looked familiar,

00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:10.458 position:50% align:center
she comes to see
our shows all the time!

00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:15.296 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:16.256 --> 00:04:17.382 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] You're that girl
with the glasses

00:04:17.465 --> 00:04:19.426 position:50% align:center
who's always in the crowd!

00:04:20.844 --> 00:04:22.262 position:50% align:center
I would've recognized
you anywhere.

00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:24.305 position:50% align:center
I am a giant fan of your work!

00:04:24.389 --> 00:04:26.850 position:50% align:center
I never would've known that you
guys were all zombies, though!

00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:28.727 position:50% align:center
And, pop goes the z-word.

00:04:28.810 --> 00:04:32.605 position:50% align:center
Well I guess this is it.
It was fun while it lasted.

00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:34.232 position:50% align:center
So now what do we do?

00:04:34.315 --> 00:04:36.818 position:50% align:center
[YUGIRI]
There's only one thing to do.

00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:38.570 position:50% align:center
We'll just have to kill her.

00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:40.238 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:04:40.321 --> 00:04:42.866 position:50% align:center
Though, I suppose there's
a less bloody solution.

00:04:42.949 --> 00:04:44.117 position:50% align:center
[ALL sigh]

00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:46.661 position:50% align:center
Oh! Please don't worry!
I mean, you guys do look

00:04:46.745 --> 00:04:48.788 position:50% align:center
pretty sickly and
banged up right now,

00:04:48.872 --> 00:04:52.042 position:50% align:center
but during a show, nobody would
ever notice you're not alive!

00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.002 position:50% align:center
You always look
so cute and beautiful

00:04:54.085 --> 00:04:55.003 position:50% align:center
when you're performing!

00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:56.963 position:50% align:center
Is that all just makeup?

00:04:57.047 --> 00:04:59.090 position:50% align:center
She's taking this like a champ.

00:04:59.174 --> 00:05:01.843 position:50% align:center
Maybe zombies just aren't
all that shocking anymore.

00:05:01.926 --> 00:05:03.094 position:50% align:center
Except you got shot!

00:05:03.178 --> 00:05:04.637 position:50% align:center
Only like two times.

00:05:04.721 --> 00:05:08.600 position:50% align:center
Hey, so, about the whole
secretly-undead-idols thing.

00:05:08.683 --> 00:05:10.727 position:50% align:center
--Could you, uh?
--Huh?

00:05:10.810 --> 00:05:13.980 position:50% align:center
Please not tell anyone!
I'm begging you!

00:05:14.064 --> 00:05:16.524 position:50% align:center
Come on, grovel already!

00:05:20.820 --> 00:05:21.821 position:50% align:center
Ca-ching!

00:05:21.905 --> 00:05:22.906 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:05:22.989 --> 00:05:24.824 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
There's an obvious fix for this!

00:05:24.908 --> 00:05:27.702 position:50% align:center
You guys should let me be
a part of Franchouchou!

00:05:27.786 --> 00:05:29.204 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:30.830 position:50% align:center
It'll be way easier
to keep the secret

00:05:30.914 --> 00:05:33.249 position:50% align:center
if I'm in the group, right?

00:05:33.333 --> 00:05:34.125 position:50% align:center
What do you mean?

00:05:34.209 --> 00:05:36.294 position:50% align:center
My, aren't you a bold one.

00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:38.421 position:50% align:center
Come on, please?

00:05:51.643 --> 00:05:52.560 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:05:52.644 --> 00:05:53.937 position:50% align:center
Huh? That was easy!

00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:55.563 position:50% align:center
You didn't think this through
for a second, did you?

00:05:55.647 --> 00:05:57.941 position:50% align:center
You can't just
let her win, man!

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:02.654 position:50% align:center
Yippee! Thank you very much!

00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:04.322 position:50% align:center
I promise I'll give it my best!

00:06:04.406 --> 00:06:06.366 position:50% align:center
You can call me Maimai Yuzuriha!

00:06:06.449 --> 00:06:09.327 position:50% align:center
And yeah, that is
actually my real name!

00:06:09.411 --> 00:06:11.204 position:50% align:center
Uh. Okay, Maimai.

00:06:11.287 --> 00:06:13.456 position:50% align:center
Sounds like something
you would name a puppy.

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:15.667 position:50% align:center
Well, it's almost curfew for me.

00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:18.211 position:50% align:center
See ya tomorrow! Bye!

00:06:19.212 --> 00:06:22.132 position:50% align:center
So she's gonna commute
instead of staying here?

00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:24.801 position:50% align:center
That's an option? What the hell.

00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:29.931 position:50% align:center
[CLASSMATE 7A]
Hey, Maimai!

00:06:30.015 --> 00:06:32.142 position:50% align:center
Let's go get some
frozen tapioca!

00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:34.561 position:50% align:center
Sorry! I'll have to
say tapi-no-ca!

00:06:34.644 --> 00:06:35.812 position:50% align:center
[CLASSMATE 7A]
Aw, man!

00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:37.772 position:50% align:center
I didn't know you had
festival stuff today.

00:06:37.856 --> 00:06:40.358 position:50% align:center
Actually it's something
way cooler than the festival!

00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:42.944 position:50% align:center
Wait, if Maimai's
bailing on tapioca, then...

00:06:43.028 --> 00:06:44.654 position:50% align:center
Hold on, do you have
a hot date or something?

00:06:44.738 --> 00:06:46.156 position:50% align:center
Tell us, now!

00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:50.702 position:50% align:center
Not in the romantic sense,
but it is a crucial rendezvous!

00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:53.955 position:50% align:center
Good morning, girls!
Maimai, reporting in!

00:06:54.956 --> 00:06:57.250 position:50% align:center
Are you dead-serious about
becoming an idol?

00:06:57.334 --> 00:06:58.293 position:50% align:center
As the grave!

00:06:58.376 --> 00:07:00.045 position:50% align:center
And you may know our secret,

00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:01.921 position:50% align:center
but you can't use
that against us.

00:07:02.005 --> 00:07:03.757 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't dare!

00:07:07.260 --> 00:07:08.261 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Fair enough.

00:07:08.345 --> 00:07:09.846 position:50% align:center
[JUNKO, SAKURA sigh]

00:07:09.929 --> 00:07:12.724 position:50% align:center
[AI] So, Maimai. Do you have
any dance experience?

00:07:12.807 --> 00:07:15.060 position:50% align:center
Nope, afraid I will be
starting off at zero!

00:07:15.143 --> 00:07:16.770 position:50% align:center
But I do have all of
the lyrics and routines

00:07:16.853 --> 00:07:18.855 position:50% align:center
memorized from all of
your shows and CDs!

00:07:18.938 --> 00:07:21.149 position:50% align:center
Are you serious?
That's so incredible!

00:07:21.232 --> 00:07:24.486 position:50% align:center
[music playing]

00:07:24.569 --> 00:07:26.112 position:50% align:center
Five. Four.

00:07:26.196 --> 00:07:27.572 position:50% align:center
Three, two, one!

00:07:27.655 --> 00:07:28.907 position:50% align:center
Now begin!

00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:30.408 position:50% align:center
Two. Three. Four.

00:07:30.492 --> 00:07:31.368 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:35.497 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Five. Six. Ready. Pose!

00:07:35.580 --> 00:07:36.873 position:50% align:center
Why are you a pretzel?

00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:38.166 position:50% align:center
I can do it perfectly
in my head,

00:07:38.249 --> 00:07:40.335 position:50% align:center
but my body's
not quite there yet!

00:07:40.418 --> 00:07:42.212 position:50% align:center
[SAKI] Look, Sakura,
she's gonna break her neck

00:07:42.295 --> 00:07:43.630 position:50% align:center
and end up like us!

00:07:43.713 --> 00:07:46.591 position:50% align:center
I'm not positive Maimai
can handle this.

00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:49.177 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Let's try again.

00:07:49.260 --> 00:07:52.055 position:50% align:center
Owwie! I'm fine,
it's not broken!

00:07:52.138 --> 00:07:53.056 position:50% align:center
[AI]
One more time.

00:07:53.139 --> 00:07:54.349 position:50% align:center
--[MAIMAI] Oof!
--[AI] And again.

00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:55.850 position:50% align:center
--[MAIMAI] D'oh!
--[AI] Again.

00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:57.644 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Fail!

00:07:57.727 --> 00:07:59.562 position:50% align:center
That's enough,
let's call it a day for now.

00:07:59.646 --> 00:08:00.855 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
I don't want to stop!

00:08:00.939 --> 00:08:02.691 position:50% align:center
I want to be a real
member of Franchouchou

00:08:02.774 --> 00:08:04.651 position:50% align:center
as soon as possible!

00:08:09.155 --> 00:08:11.825 position:50% align:center
[AI] Make sure to practice
what we did today, okay?

00:08:11.908 --> 00:08:14.160 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Right-o! I'll see you tomorrow!

00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:18.498 position:50% align:center
[SAKI gasps]
Dude. You're kidding me.

00:08:18.581 --> 00:08:20.375 position:50% align:center
[SAKI gasps]
It's in color!

00:08:20.458 --> 00:08:22.460 position:50% align:center
Sakura, look,
this thing's in color!

00:08:22.544 --> 00:08:23.962 position:50% align:center
Oh yeah, that is cool!

00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:25.839 position:50% align:center
Does it have Oyajitchi?

00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:26.881 position:50% align:center
Yeah, he's there!

00:08:26.965 --> 00:08:29.259 position:50% align:center
It's the 20th
anniversary edition!

00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:34.431 position:50% align:center
Wicked! I'd be pissed if
he wasn't! Love that guy!

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.142 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
You worked really hard today!

00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:38.977 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
I've got a lot to learn.

00:08:39.060 --> 00:08:41.312 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] You impressed Ai
with the energy you brought.

00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:44.482 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] I just want
everyone to accept me.

00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:48.194 position:50% align:center
So, how long have you been
a Franchouchou superfan?

00:08:48.278 --> 00:08:51.239 position:50% align:center
Well, I was beginning
to give up on Saga.

00:08:51.322 --> 00:08:52.615 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:52.699 --> 00:08:55.952 position:50% align:center
Then I realized, this place
has a lot of potential.

00:08:56.036 --> 00:08:57.954 position:50% align:center
But nobody knows that!

00:08:58.038 --> 00:09:00.707 position:50% align:center
Guess that's just part of
Saga's thing, I figure.

00:09:00.790 --> 00:09:03.335 position:50% align:center
Like, if Saga were Fukuoka,
everyone would think of it as

00:09:03.418 --> 00:09:05.420 position:50% align:center
a lively place with
active residents.

00:09:05.503 --> 00:09:06.921 position:50% align:center
And then, people
would probably care

00:09:07.005 --> 00:09:08.465 position:50% align:center
about it a whole lot more!

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:11.051 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] Yeah, Saga is
kind of its own thing.

00:09:11.134 --> 00:09:13.887 position:50% align:center
Anyway, one day I was
flipping through Sagazine.

00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:17.349 position:50% align:center
And I was like,
"Whoa! Idols in Saga?"

00:09:17.432 --> 00:09:18.516 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:19.893 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
I saw that you were doing a show

00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:21.895 position:50% align:center
at the end of the year.

00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:27.859 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:43.083 --> 00:09:45.710 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:45.794 --> 00:09:47.295 position:50% align:center
Y'liked it that much?

00:09:47.379 --> 00:09:49.422 position:50% align:center
It was totally mindblowing!

00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:51.216 position:50% align:center
Oh gosh, thank you.

00:09:51.299 --> 00:09:53.009 position:50% align:center
I don't know how to
say it, but I'm amazed

00:09:53.093 --> 00:09:55.053 position:50% align:center
at your expression
whenever you sing.

00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:57.472 position:50% align:center
The way you're able to
shine so brightly!

00:09:57.555 --> 00:09:58.932 position:50% align:center
It got me thinking
more and more about

00:09:59.015 --> 00:10:00.684 position:50% align:center
how I wanted to be just like you

00:10:00.767 --> 00:10:02.352 position:50% align:center
and live a super-cool
life in Saga

00:10:02.435 --> 00:10:04.562 position:50% align:center
the same way you
and your friends do!

00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:10.694 position:50% align:center
You are just like me.

00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:13.279 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] But the EFS
show was a real mess.

00:10:13.363 --> 00:10:15.573 position:50% align:center
Trust me, we felt it
in the crowd, too.

00:10:15.657 --> 00:10:17.575 position:50% align:center
I have never wished
that I could make my voice

00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:19.244 position:50% align:center
ring out louder than
I did that day

00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.955 position:50% align:center
watching my favs
up on that stage.

00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:27.419 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
But. When you played Saga Arena,

00:10:27.502 --> 00:10:31.131 position:50% align:center
I realized how amazing
you guys truly are!

00:10:31.214 --> 00:10:35.260 position:50% align:center
You may be zombies, but you're
just as alive as anyone!

00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:36.928 position:50% align:center
So, I don't think you
need to worry too much

00:10:37.012 --> 00:10:39.764 position:50% align:center
about makeup and
superficial stuff like that!

00:10:39.848 --> 00:10:41.558 position:50% align:center
Because being able to
perform the way you do

00:10:41.641 --> 00:10:43.852 position:50% align:center
is loads more special!

00:10:43.935 --> 00:10:46.646 position:50% align:center
I know that I can't
contribute much yet.

00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:51.026 position:50% align:center
But I am willing to do whatever
I can for Franchouchou!

00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:55.030 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
We'll work hard together!

00:10:55.113 --> 00:10:56.573 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
Yeah!

00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:58.408 position:50% align:center
[CLASS PRESIDENT 7A]
We're pathetic!

00:10:58.491 --> 00:11:01.244 position:50% align:center
We put all our heads together
and this is the best we can do?

00:11:01.327 --> 00:11:03.079 position:50% align:center
[CLASSMATE 7C] Let's just go
with the beauty pageant again

00:11:03.163 --> 00:11:04.247 position:50% align:center
and be done with it.

00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:05.915 position:50% align:center
But that's a cop-out!

00:11:05.999 --> 00:11:08.126 position:50% align:center
Not that any of these
plans are better!

00:11:08.209 --> 00:11:10.462 position:50% align:center
Can't we eke out
one decent idea--

00:11:10.545 --> 00:11:13.882 position:50% align:center
Ca-ching!

00:11:13.965 --> 00:11:16.259 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
A school festival show?

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:17.969 position:50% align:center
If we get popular with
high-school students,

00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:19.846 position:50% align:center
it'll really help
with visibility!

00:11:19.929 --> 00:11:22.390 position:50% align:center
The crowds will be
so crazy! Trust me!

00:11:22.474 --> 00:11:24.309 position:50% align:center
Ei-yah! Chouchou!

00:11:24.392 --> 00:11:26.644 position:50% align:center
Ei-yah! Chouchou! See?

00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:28.730 position:50% align:center
Ei-yah! Chouchou!

00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.523 position:50% align:center
High-schoolers, huh?

00:11:30.607 --> 00:11:31.649 position:50% align:center
Sounds like fun!

00:11:31.733 --> 00:11:34.235 position:50% align:center
A worthwhile endeavor,
I would say!

00:11:34.319 --> 00:11:36.029 position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:11:38.823 --> 00:11:41.659 position:50% align:center
[SAKI] Wipe that stupid smile
off or I will!

00:11:41.743 --> 00:11:43.203 position:50% align:center
[KOTARO] The crowd
you girls tend to attract

00:11:43.286 --> 00:11:46.164 position:50% align:center
is a hodgepodge of
losers and freaks.

00:11:46.247 --> 00:11:47.415 position:50% align:center
Let's take aim at
the demographic

00:11:47.499 --> 00:11:49.167 position:50% align:center
that'll shape Saga's future.

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:50.669 position:50% align:center
'Kay, what about Maimai?

00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:53.546 position:50% align:center
She can't get through a routine
without hurting herself.

00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:56.549 position:50% align:center
Then get it together quick,
'cause she's the star.

00:11:56.633 --> 00:11:58.051 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:58.134 --> 00:12:00.512 position:50% align:center
[KOTARO] This concert marks
the rebirth of Franchouchou

00:12:00.595 --> 00:12:03.598 position:50% align:center
as a group of eight,
and the debut of Number Seven!

00:12:03.682 --> 00:12:04.641 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:06.393 position:50% align:center
Do you think you're
ready for this?

00:12:06.476 --> 00:12:09.688 position:50% align:center
Huh? As long as my body
doesn't betray me, yes!

00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:11.439 position:50% align:center
Then all you gotta do
is practice your butt off

00:12:11.523 --> 00:12:12.649 position:50% align:center
until the show!

00:12:12.732 --> 00:12:14.776 position:50% align:center
Now let me see your game face!

00:12:14.859 --> 00:12:18.279 position:50% align:center
Okay! Come on, mind and body,
please be in sync for once!

00:12:18.363 --> 00:12:21.449 position:50% align:center
The new Franchouchou is
gonna rock all their socks off!

00:12:21.533 --> 00:12:23.702 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Yeah!

00:12:44.931 --> 00:12:46.307 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Great! You've got it!

00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:47.600 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Awesome!

00:12:47.684 --> 00:12:50.311 position:50% align:center
I see you managed to
remain upright this time.

00:12:50.395 --> 00:12:52.939 position:50% align:center
Two days 'til the show.
That was close!

00:12:53.023 --> 00:12:56.860 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Thanks for
supporting me!

00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:59.237 position:50% align:center
Hey, this calls for
a group outing!

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:01.239 position:50% align:center
Let's hit the public bath!

00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:02.741 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:13:02.824 --> 00:13:04.576 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] It's kinda my thing!
I know some great spots--

00:13:04.659 --> 00:13:06.036 position:50% align:center
I hate to say it, Maimai,

00:13:06.119 --> 00:13:08.955 position:50% align:center
but we're gonna have to
pass on that one.

00:13:09.039 --> 00:13:10.999 position:50% align:center
[JUNKO]
Not that we don't like baths.

00:13:11.082 --> 00:13:13.209 position:50% align:center
But they're kinda
a dead giveaway.

00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:16.296 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Oh my gosh!
I'm so sorry, I forgot!

00:13:16.379 --> 00:13:18.131 position:50% align:center
[LILY] It's fine! Actually,
it might be fun to

00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:20.175 position:50% align:center
go and check out
your school instead!

00:13:20.258 --> 00:13:22.427 position:50% align:center
Nice! That way we can
take over their turf!

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.304 position:50% align:center
Whoa, chill!

00:13:24.387 --> 00:13:27.057 position:50% align:center
I don't have a lot of memories
from high school, actually.

00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:28.266 position:50% align:center
Yeah, neither do I.

00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:30.018 position:50% align:center
I'd be interested to see
how the young people

00:13:30.101 --> 00:13:31.728 position:50% align:center
of today spend their youth.

00:13:31.811 --> 00:13:33.271 position:50% align:center
Great, let's do it!

00:13:33.355 --> 00:13:35.273 position:50% align:center
I can get permission
from my teacher!

00:13:35.357 --> 00:13:37.859 position:50% align:center
Oh, boy!

00:13:37.942 --> 00:13:40.779 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 7A] Hurry up,
the festival's tomorrow!

00:13:42.530 --> 00:13:45.825 position:50% align:center
That was such a drag,
right? [gasps]

00:13:45.909 --> 00:13:48.661 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] I'm sorry.
The others kind of took off.

00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:50.080 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
No worries!

00:13:50.163 --> 00:13:51.539 position:50% align:center
Everyone's pumped about
the cultural festival tomorrow,

00:13:51.623 --> 00:13:52.749 position:50% align:center
so they're sure to run into

00:13:52.832 --> 00:13:54.709 position:50% align:center
excited students
wherever they go!

00:13:54.793 --> 00:13:58.129 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] You're right, the prep
always was half the fun.

00:13:58.213 --> 00:13:59.422 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI]
So, what were you like

00:13:59.506 --> 00:14:01.257 position:50% align:center
in your high school
days, Sakura?

00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:04.094 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Mm... Kinda dead on the inside.

00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:05.095 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:14:05.178 --> 00:14:06.221 position:50% align:center
Well ya see...

00:14:06.304 --> 00:14:08.807 position:50% align:center
Some disappointing
stuff happened.

00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:11.851 position:50% align:center
So I had trouble
taking anything seriously.

00:14:11.935 --> 00:14:13.978 position:50% align:center
Are you saying that
you'd lost all hope?

00:14:14.062 --> 00:14:17.482 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] Mm-hm.
But then I saw Iron Frill,

00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:19.901 position:50% align:center
and I was so inspired by Ai
and the rest of the group

00:14:19.984 --> 00:14:23.738 position:50% align:center
that I built up the strength
to keep moving forward!

00:14:23.822 --> 00:14:25.073 position:50% align:center
Around that time,
you could always

00:14:25.156 --> 00:14:27.617 position:50% align:center
find me practicing in
a corner of the classroom,

00:14:27.701 --> 00:14:29.369 position:50% align:center
so I was super happy
when I found out

00:14:29.452 --> 00:14:31.996 position:50% align:center
they were auditioning
new members!

00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:36.668 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA] But then I died
before I got to apply.

00:14:36.751 --> 00:14:38.712 position:50% align:center
Being a zombie isn't
all bad though.

00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:40.922 position:50% align:center
Because now I get
another chance.

00:14:41.006 --> 00:14:42.340 position:50% align:center
After meeting the
rest of the group,

00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:45.010 position:50% align:center
I feel like I can
take on any challenge!

00:14:45.093 --> 00:14:48.054 position:50% align:center
Even an EFS do-over show!

00:14:48.138 --> 00:14:49.014 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:14:49.097 --> 00:14:50.056 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Hm?

00:14:50.140 --> 00:14:52.017 position:50% align:center
Wait, what? You're going back?

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:53.268 position:50% align:center
Nobody told you that?

00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:54.853 position:50% align:center
Definitely not!

00:14:54.936 --> 00:14:57.689 position:50% align:center
That was a catastrophe
for you, remember?

00:14:57.772 --> 00:15:00.316 position:50% align:center
Why would you want to
do that to yourself again?

00:15:01.609 --> 00:15:03.236 position:50% align:center
That's who Franchouchou is.

00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:04.779 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:15:04.863 --> 00:15:05.780 position:50% align:center
Look, I know.

00:15:05.864 --> 00:15:07.907 position:50% align:center
EFS was a total mistake.

00:15:07.991 --> 00:15:09.659 position:50% align:center
We ended up in debt
and we couldn't even

00:15:09.743 --> 00:15:12.370 position:50% align:center
do idol stuff for
a pretty long time.

00:15:12.454 --> 00:15:14.122 position:50% align:center
But still, none of us gave up.

00:15:14.205 --> 00:15:15.248 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:15:15.331 --> 00:15:16.666 position:50% align:center
Sure, it's scary
to think something

00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:17.959 position:50% align:center
like that could happen again,

00:15:18.043 --> 00:15:20.253 position:50% align:center
but if we're together,
we can face anything!

00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:24.257 position:50% align:center
And I mean, if we ever
gave up trying, that'd be worse.

00:15:24.341 --> 00:15:27.010 position:50% align:center
We'd be wandering lost
with the rest of the dead.

00:15:27.093 --> 00:15:28.803 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI gasps]

00:15:28.887 --> 00:15:30.638 position:50% align:center
[SAKURA]
Our hearts may not beat anymore,

00:15:30.722 --> 00:15:31.848 position:50% align:center
but we're still living,

00:15:31.931 --> 00:15:34.517 position:50% align:center
because we refuse to
quit chasing our dreams!

00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:36.936 position:50% align:center
We keep rising from the ashes!

00:15:38.897 --> 00:15:40.440 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Oh my gosh,
I'm so sorry!

00:15:40.523 --> 00:15:43.693 position:50% align:center
That came out really corny
and kinda conceited, huh?

00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:46.321 position:50% align:center
What's the matter?

00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:48.198 position:50% align:center
So, that's who
Franchouchou is.

00:15:48.281 --> 00:15:49.449 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:15:49.532 --> 00:15:51.326 position:50% align:center
And now that we have you
as part of the group,

00:15:51.409 --> 00:15:53.036 position:50% align:center
we're even stronger!

00:15:53.119 --> 00:15:56.873 position:50% align:center
Let's make sure that we put on
an amazing show tomorrow, 'kay?

00:15:56.956 --> 00:15:58.249 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:15:58.333 --> 00:16:01.419 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] That's who
Franchouchou's Number One is!

00:16:01.503 --> 00:16:04.214 position:50% align:center
Uh. Hey, are you
okay there, Maimai?

00:16:04.297 --> 00:16:07.592 position:50% align:center
I think maybe you missed
the point of my entire speech.

00:16:07.676 --> 00:16:09.594 position:50% align:center
Hang on a sec!

00:16:09.678 --> 00:16:11.638 position:50% align:center
Did you forget something?

00:16:11.721 --> 00:16:13.640 position:50% align:center
You know, me?

00:16:21.022 --> 00:16:22.899 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Maimai. Don't worry.

00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:25.235 position:50% align:center
You've practiced hard
for this show.

00:16:25.318 --> 00:16:26.277 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:16:26.361 --> 00:16:28.613 position:50% align:center
Sweet! Let's get out
there and rock!

00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:30.490 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Right!

00:16:32.242 --> 00:16:33.076 position:50% align:center
Here we go!

00:16:33.159 --> 00:16:34.619 position:50% align:center
So excited!

00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:44.170 position:50% align:center
[singing]

00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:45.588 position:50% align:center
[BULK]
Huh? Who's that?

00:16:45.672 --> 00:16:47.674 position:50% align:center
They've got a new member!

00:16:49.426 --> 00:16:51.344 position:50% align:center
[CLASSMATE 7A]
Whoa! Is that Maimai?

00:16:51.428 --> 00:16:52.804 position:50% align:center
What is happening?

00:16:52.887 --> 00:16:58.893 position:50% align:center
[singing]

00:18:33.863 --> 00:18:38.284 position:50% align:center
[SCHOOL cheering]

00:18:38.368 --> 00:18:39.911 position:50% align:center
That was so awesome, Maimai!

00:18:39.994 --> 00:18:43.039 position:50% align:center
You're the star of
the Saganan Carnival Maimai!

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:45.583 position:50% align:center
[SAKI] Hey, what's up?
We're Franchouchou!

00:18:45.667 --> 00:18:48.086 position:50% align:center
Today is our first time
performing at a school festival,

00:18:48.169 --> 00:18:49.587 position:50% align:center
so thank you for having us here!

00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:51.464 position:50% align:center
And not just that,
but from now on,

00:18:51.548 --> 00:18:54.300 position:50% align:center
we officially have a new member!

00:18:55.802 --> 00:19:00.348 position:50% align:center
Hello, my name is Number Seven!
It's nice to meet you all!

00:19:00.432 --> 00:19:02.517 position:50% align:center
[CLASSMATES]
She's an idol now?

00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:04.394 position:50% align:center
Dang, that came outta nowhere!

00:19:04.477 --> 00:19:06.521 position:50% align:center
This lot sure
keeps you on your toes!

00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:09.357 position:50% align:center
Listen to what Seven has to say!

00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:11.401 position:50% align:center
Knock 'em dead, newbie!

00:19:15.822 --> 00:19:17.115 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] First and foremost,
I want to thank

00:19:17.198 --> 00:19:18.700 position:50% align:center
each and every one
of you for coming

00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:20.368 position:50% align:center
to the Saganan Carnival today!

00:19:20.452 --> 00:19:21.995 position:50% align:center
It really means the world to us!

00:19:22.078 --> 00:19:24.247 position:50% align:center
[SCHOOL cheers]

00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:26.332 position:50% align:center
And now, if you all don't mind.

00:19:26.416 --> 00:19:27.959 position:50% align:center
I have one more announcement.

00:19:28.043 --> 00:19:29.336 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:35.550 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] You see,
after today's show is over,

00:19:35.633 --> 00:19:37.218 position:50% align:center
I will be graduating.

00:19:37.302 --> 00:19:39.721 position:50% align:center
Leaving Franchouchou!

00:19:39.804 --> 00:19:43.516 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Huh?

00:19:44.517 --> 00:19:47.187 position:50% align:center
And now, I hope you'll
enjoy "Into the Light,"

00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:48.688 position:50% align:center
my last song.

00:19:48.772 --> 00:19:49.981 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:20:04.329 --> 00:20:10.335 position:50% align:center
[singing]

00:20:27.018 --> 00:20:28.520 position:50% align:center
I've been thinking
about it a lot,

00:20:28.603 --> 00:20:31.022 position:50% align:center
ever since I had that talk
with Sakura yesterday.

00:20:31.106 --> 00:20:33.149 position:50% align:center
And my mind's made up.

00:20:33.233 --> 00:20:34.859 position:50% align:center
I thought I was
the same as you guys

00:20:34.943 --> 00:20:37.987 position:50% align:center
despite being alive,
but I was wrong.

00:20:38.071 --> 00:20:39.239 position:50% align:center
It's not your cold skin

00:20:39.322 --> 00:20:40.990 position:50% align:center
or lack of heartbeat, either.

00:20:41.074 --> 00:20:42.742 position:50% align:center
None of you were
alive for very long,

00:20:42.826 --> 00:20:44.202 position:50% align:center
but I think each
of you lived out

00:20:44.285 --> 00:20:46.913 position:50% align:center
your short lives with
everything you had.

00:20:46.996 --> 00:20:49.207 position:50% align:center
The reason you shine
so bright is because,

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:51.835 position:50% align:center
even after dying,
you keep rising again.

00:20:51.918 --> 00:20:53.169 position:50% align:center
It's like you're
dead-set on living

00:20:53.253 --> 00:20:55.588 position:50% align:center
your afterlife to the fullest!

00:20:55.672 --> 00:20:58.258 position:50% align:center
I think, if I want to
shine like that,

00:20:58.341 --> 00:21:01.845 position:50% align:center
the first step is making the
most of my life here in Saga.

00:21:01.928 --> 00:21:05.682 position:50% align:center
That's why I'm gonna graduate
from Franchouchou and live!

00:21:05.765 --> 00:21:08.601 position:50% align:center
Here and now, in the Reiwa era!

00:21:09.602 --> 00:21:12.814 position:50% align:center
[MAIMAI] Okay! That was
all I wanted to say!

00:21:12.897 --> 00:21:16.443 position:50% align:center
And with that, adieu!

00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:22.532 position:50% align:center
[singing]

00:21:31.875 --> 00:21:36.087 position:50% align:center
[SCHOOL cheers]

00:21:38.089 --> 00:21:40.383 position:50% align:center
[AI] You've got a ton
of amazing qualities.

00:21:40.467 --> 00:21:42.218 position:50% align:center
[JUNKO]
You came through like a storm.

00:21:42.302 --> 00:21:44.346 position:50% align:center
[LILY] Yeah, your name
might as well be Bye-Bye.

00:21:44.429 --> 00:21:45.764 position:50% align:center
[YUGIRI]
Don't ever forget the courage

00:21:45.847 --> 00:21:47.807 position:50% align:center
that brought you this far.

00:21:47.891 --> 00:21:50.185 position:50% align:center
It's been such an honor
to share the stage with you.

00:21:50.268 --> 00:21:52.562 position:50% align:center
Look us up when you
croak for real, 'kay?

00:21:52.645 --> 00:21:55.690 position:50% align:center
'Kay! Oh, this is for you.

00:21:57.233 --> 00:21:58.360 position:50% align:center
[SAKI]
Huh?

00:21:58.443 --> 00:22:00.612 position:50% align:center
But I can't take this,
